    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="143"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d143fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London,
                        via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-22">22 October
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 632, Personal and Top Secret, from the President to the Prime
                    Minister.</p>
                <p>Your 795,<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn2">Not printed.</note> 796,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d143fn3">Not printed.</note> 797,<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> 799,<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn5">Not printed.</note>
                        800<note n="2" xml:id="d143fn6">Not printed.</note> and 801<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d143fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> received.</p>
                <p>I am delighted to learn of your success at Moscow in making progress toward a
                    compromise solution of the Polish problem.</p>
                <p>When and if a solution is arrived at, I should like to be consulted as to the
                    advisability from this point of view of delaying its publication for about two
                    weeks. You will understand.</p>
                <p>Everything is going well here at the present time.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
